Embeddings are dense vector representations produced by deep learning models. They capture semantic meaning,
allowing vector databases to retrieve documents with similar meaning instead of relying only on exact keyword matches.

"Embeddings are numerical vector representations generated by deep learning models. They capture semantic meaning so that similar texts are close together in vector space."


Tokenization is a preprocessing step, while the embedding layer is the first learnable layer of the neural network that converts token IDs into dense vector representations.
❓ Is tokenization part of Deep Learning?
❓ Who creates embeddings?
❓ Is the embedding layer part of the neural network?



❓ Who creates embeddings?

👉 The embedding layer of the neural network creates them.

But another question arises:

Who taught the embedding layer to create meaningful embeddings?

Answer:

👉 The Deep Learning training process.


Embeddings are generated by the embedding layer, which is the first learnable layer of the neural network.
During training, this layer learns meaningful vector representations by updating its weights. 
During inference, it uses those learned weights to convert token IDs into embeddings that are passed to the transformer layers.


Embedding Layer is a Deep Learning concept.
Every LLM uses an embedding layer.

NLP → Why we need tokenization (text preprocessing).
